                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.602/91: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-28T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1923—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>207. Mission’s 467 of June 27. View which you expressed to Payne that proposed
                    change in article 2 does not satisfy our objections as to the principle involved
                    has the Department’s approval. If the protocol is adopted with the changes which
                    you indicate, you should, therefore, make the statement transmitted in our
                    telegram 186 of June 16.<note n="32" xml:id="d870fn32">Not printed; see telegram
                        no. 244, June 23, to the Ambassador in France, <ref target="#pg_1023">p.
                            1023</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
